# GitHub CLI (`gh`) Usage

Always pass `--repo cognitedata/toolkit` (or `-R cognitedata/toolkit`) on every `gh` command to ensure you never accidentally target a fork or different repository.

```bash
# Good
gh pr list --repo cognitedata/toolkit
gh api repos/cognitedata/toolkit/pulls/123/comments

# Bad â€” relies on auto-detection from git remote
gh pr list
```

For `gh api` calls, always use the full `repos/cognitedata/toolkit/...` path explicitly.
